  "body": "I tried the json file in docs/downward API. After the pod is created, the environment variables are created but have empty value:\n\n```\n$ docker exec cca073ac2d66 env | grep \"POD\"\nPOD_NAMESPACE=\nPOD_NAME=\n```\n\nThe json file in the doc has a few grammar issues, so I modified it a bit:\n\n```\n{\n  \"apiVersion\":\"v1beta3\",\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"name\": \"downward-api-pod\"\n  },\n  \"kind\": \"Pod\",\n  \"spec\": {\n      \"containers\": [{\n        \"name\": \"example-container\",\n        \"image\": \"gcr.io/google_containers/busybox\",\n        \"env\": [{\n          \"name\": \"POD_NAMESPACE\",\n          \"valueFrom\": {\n            \"fieldPath\": {\n              \"apiVersion\": \"v1beta3\",\n              \"fieldPath\": \"metadata.namespace\"\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"POD_NAME\",\n          \"valueFrom\": {\n            \"fieldPath\": {\n              \"apiVersion\": \"v1beta3\",\n              \"fieldPath\": \"metadata.name\"\n            }\n          }\n        }]\n      }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n@lavalamp @dchen1107 @pmorie\n",
